  "description": "Rapid formant morphing between all vowel positions via LFO1, but at extremely slow rate. The voice cycles through A-E-I-O-U over 30 seconds, creating the impression of someone speaking an unknown language in slow motion. Each vowel shape colors the partial cloud differently, so the timbre is constantly evolving.",
